statements: SELECT * FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE id = 1;
SELECT ml_insights FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE id = 2;
SELECT data_pattern, data_distribution FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE id = 3;
SELECT * FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE data_pattern LIKE '%classification%';
SELECT * FROM MachineLearningInsights ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT * FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE id = 100;
SELECT data_pattern, data_distribution FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE data_pattern LIKE 'Supervised%' ORDER BY data_distribution ASC;
SELECT id, data_pattern, ml_insights FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE data_distribution NOT LIKE '%Special%' ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT * FROM MachineLearningInsights WHERE data_distribution IN ('Evenly Distributed', 'Skewed') AND LENGTH(ml_insights) > 1000;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_records FROM MachineLearningInsights;
SELECT * FROM Machine_Learning_Insights;
SELECT id, insight_description FROM Machine_Learning_Insights WHERE distribution = 'Normal';
SELECT id, algorithm_name, accuracy FROM ML_Algorithms WHERE model_type = 'Regression' ORDER BY accuracy DESC;
SELECT id, algorithm_name, training_time FROM ML_Algorithms WHERE accuracy > 90;
SELECT algorithm_name, model_type, accuracy FROM ML_Algorithms ORDER BY model_type ASC, accuracy DESC;
SELECT id, insight_description, data_pattern FROM Machine_Learning_Insights WHERE data_pattern = 'Supervised Learning' ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT algorithm_name, model_type, accuracy FROM ML_Algorithms WHERE accuracy > 0.85 ORDER BY accuracy DESC, algorithm_name ASC;
SELECT id, algorithm_name, model_type, accuracy FROM ML_Algorithms WHERE model_type = 'Classification' AND accuracy BETWEEN 0.7 AND 0.9 ORDER BY id ASC;
SELECT * FROM Machine_Learning_Insights, ML_Algorithms WHERE Machine_Learning_Insights.id = ML_Algorithms.id;
SELECT algorithm_name, AVG(accuracy) AS avg_accuracy, MAX(training_time) AS max_training_time FROM ML_Algorithms GROUP BY algorithm_name HAVING AVG(accuracy) > 0.8;
SELECT column1, column2, column3 FROM Table1;
SELECT column2, column1, column3 FROM Table2;
SELECT column3, column1, column2 FROM Table3;
SELECT * FROM Table1 WHERE column1 > 100;
SELECT column1, column2 FROM Table2 WHERE column3 = '2021-01-01';
SELECT * FROM Table1 WHERE column1 > 10 ORDER BY column2 DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT column2, column3 FROM Table2 WHERE column1 = 'value' ORDER BY column3 ASC;
SELECT DISTINCT column1 FROM Table3 WHERE column2 LIKE '%pattern%' AND column3 = TRUE;
SELECT column1, column2 FROM Table1 JOIN Table2 ON Table1.column1 = Table2.column2 WHERE Table1.column3 < 100 ORDER BY Table2.column3 DESC;
SELECT AVG(column3) AS average_value FROM Table1 GROUP BY column2 HAVING average_value > 50;
SELECT * FROM data_patterns ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT column_1, column_3 FROM data_patterns WHERE column_2 = 'value' LIMIT 10;
SELECT id, label FROM data_distributions WHERE label = 1;
SELECT query_name, query_text FROM data_analysis_queries ORDER BY query_name ASC LIMIT 5;
SELECT model_name, accuracy, precision FROM machine_learning_insights WHERE accuracy > 0.8;
SELECT * FROM data_patterns WHERE column_1 = 'value1';
SELECT column_2, column_3 FROM data_patterns WHERE id = 5;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_rows FROM data_patterns;
SELECT feature_1, feature_2 FROM data_distributions WHERE label = 1 ORDER BY feature_1 DESC;
SELECT model_name, accuracy, precision, recall FROM machine_learning_insights WHERE accuracy > 0.8;
SELECT * FROM data_patterns;
SELECT id, feature_1, label FROM data_patterns ORDER BY label DESC;
SELECT category, value FROM distributions WHERE value > 0.5;
SELECT model_name, accuracy FROM machine_learning WHERE accuracy >= 0.8 ORDER BY accuracy DESC;
SELECT analysis_date, insights FROM insights WHERE analysis_date >= '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM data_patterns WHERE label = 'positive';
SELECT id, feature_1, feature_2 FROM data_patterns WHERE feature_1 > 0.5 AND feature_2 < 0.3;
SELECT * FROM distributions WHERE value BETWEEN 0.1 AND 0.5 ORDER BY value DESC;
SELECT model_name, accuracy FROM machine_learning WHERE accuracy >= 0.8 ORDER BY accuracy DESC;
SELECT id, pattern_name, count FROM patterns_analysis WHERE count > 100 ORDER BY count DESC;
